The paper deals with a communication system involving multiple antennas at the reader and tag ends, which is a typical topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed scheme involves unitary matrices, which are commonly used in signal processing and control theory (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the performance improvement of the system, which can be evaluated using machine learning techniques (cs.MM) and statistical analysis (cs.LG).
